    "Html": "<p>I've got a Presenter approach to PRISM in place. I've found that for some reason my view's won't register if i do it via the myRegion.Add(MyViewInstance), myRegion.Activate(MyViewInstance).</p>\r\n<p>They do however work if i approach it from regionManager.RegisterViewRegion().</p>\r\n<p>eg:</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\">DspWelcome</span></span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:x-small\"> dspwelcomeview = </span><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\">new</span></span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:x-small\"> </span><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\">DspWelcome</span></span><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">();<br><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\">IRegion</span></span><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"> welcomeRegion = regionManager.Regions[</span><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#2b91af;font-size:x-small\">RegionNames</span></span><span style=\"font-size:x-small\">.WelcomeRegion];<br><span style=\"font-size:x-small\">welcomeRegion.Add(dspwelcomeview, </span><span style=\"color:#a31515;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#a31515;font-size:x-small\">&quot;view_welcome&quot;</span></span><span style=\"font-size:x-small\">, </span><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-size:x-small\">false</span></span><span style=\"font-size:x-small\">);<br><span style=\"font-size:x-small\">welcomeRegion.Activate(dspwelcomeview);</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\">Nothing shows on screen? if i do this however:<br><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\">regionManager.RegisterViewWithRegion(RegionNames.WelcomeRegion, typeof(DspWelcome));</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\">Disco! :) ...shown. What step am I missing is more my point here? as it feels as whilst a new-up a DspWelcome() its still not being added to the WelcomeRegion's display children?</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"><span style=\"color:#008000;font-size:x-small\"></span></span></p>",
